<h1>Places of Interest</h1>

<p align="justify"><strong>Pla&ccedil;a Catalunya</strong> is a large square in the center of town and an important point of reference. It is the transfer point for several bus, night-bus, Metro and train lines and has a tourist information office
that offers maps, guides, tickets and additional information. Extending from Pla?a Catalunya is the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/La-Rambla/_xMCfM9AMDl_lKCezjRpMoGJiIpYeTZYhe7lbJhRdnng"><strong><u>Rambla</u></strong></a>, a bustling avenue famous for the vivid colors of its flower stalls. Here you will find the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Boqueria-Market/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xeqmRURyj3aPg"><strong><u>Boqueria Market</u></strong></a> and the city's opera house, the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Gran-Teatre-del-Liceu/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xe3THyc-7MBJI"><strong><u>Teatre del Liceu</u></strong></a>. The Rambla ends at the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Mirador-de-Colom/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xedxFbHAgVZrs"><strong><u>Columbus Monument</u></strong></a> that overlooks the city&#8217;s harbor. Not far beyond, on a pier in the middle of the city&#8217;s harbor, is Maremagnum, a large shopping and entertainment center.</p>

<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="La boqueria" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-825-Imagen/Mercat-Boqueria.2.jpg">

<p align="justify">Just off the Rambla is the old town or Gothic Quarter (<a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Barri-Gotic/_xMCfM9AMDl_lKCezjRpMoM4l2_IxcOwopIHluCmpvC8"><strong><u>Barri G&ograve;tic</u></strong></a>). This captivating neighborhood of narrow streets and bohemian atmosphere is well worth exploring: one will discover Roman ruins, Gothic buildings and many historical monuments. Of particular interest is the impressive 13th century Cathedral and Pla&ccedil;a Reial, a square whose two central lampposts were <strong>Antoni Gaud&iacute;</strong>'s first commission in Barcelona. Crossing Via Laietana one enters the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/The-old-Born-Market/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xeEd8PDpUgKLI"><strong><u>Born</u></strong></a> neighborhood, which houses the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.com/Museu-Picasso/_xMCfM9AMDl9TqoTN2UCZ-c8IpfMZussssXJNW3-gw_z7Oo4p1EAABCqxqGMNX2d5"><strong><u>Picasso Museum</u></strong></a> and the church of <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Santa-Maria-del-Mar/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xe7rhAgUa92B0"><strong><u>Santa Maria del Mar</u></strong></a>.</p>

<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="Barri g&ograve;tic" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-479-Imagen/Barri-Gotic.Barcelona.jpg">

<p align="justify">The <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Port-Vell/_xMCfM9AMDl_lKCezjRpMoE3e9-e2bg7M4O0vc1z3nFw"><strong><u>Port Vell</u></strong></a> and <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Port-Olimpic/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xeLgfwzE58hfY"><strong><u>Port Ol&iacute;mpic</u></strong></a> are located along the harbor and shore, respectively, and are lined with many restaurants, bars, shops and recreational areas. Nearby are over four kilometers of beaches equipped with the most modern in amenities.</p>

<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="Port" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-495-Imagen/Port-Vell.Barcelona.jpg">

<p align="justify">One of the dominant features of Barcelona's geography is <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Parc-de-Montjuic/_xMCfM9AMDl_lKCezjRpMoMhr-AZA4XHP4btJkzuN28w"><strong><u>Montju&iuml;c</u></strong></a>, the mountain that rises at the southern edge of the city. Its integration into the city began with the 1929 Universal Exposition and was recently completed for the 1992 Olympics. Today it houses museums, parks and important exposition centers such as the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.com/Museu-Nacional-d-Art-de-Catalunya---MNAC/_xMCfM9AMDl9TqoTN2UCZ-c8IpfMZussssXJNW3-gw_yFKhVqvXib98BsLsWO24aZ"><strong><u>Museu Nacional d'Art de Catalunya</u></strong></a>, the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.com/Fundacio-Joan-Miro/_xMCfM9AMDl9TqoTN2UCZ-c8IpfMZussssXJNW3-gw_z7Oo4p1EAABLBOEDJZ_j9L"><strong><u>Fundaci&oacute;  Joan Mir&oacute;</u> </strong></a> museum, the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/El-Poble-Espanyol/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xeG2maiZHrkk4"><strong><u>Poble Espanyol</u></strong></a>,
the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Estadi-Olimpic-Lluis-Companys/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xe8B3OhEdx04o"><strong><u>Olympic Stadium</u></strong></a> and the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Palau-Sant-Jordi/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xe5RSebZ3Xv9k"><strong><u>Palau Sant Jordi</u></strong></a> arena.</p>

<p align="justify">The grid of streets that make up much of central Barcelona was designed in the 1860's by Ildelfons Cerd&agrave; and is known as the <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Quadrat-d-or/_xMCfM9AMDl_lKCezjRpMoEgDWFmm-Kfv0eohZuetgkY"><strong><u>Eixample</u></strong></a>. Its main boulevard, <strong>Passeig de Gr&agrave;cia</strong>, and the adjacent <strong>Rambla Catalunya</strong>, are lined with shops, hotels and cafes. On Passeig de Gr&agrave;cia one can find Modernista masterpieces such as Antoni Gaud&iacute;'s <a href="http://bcnshop.barcelonaturisme.com/vis?prod=18555&amp;leng=1"><strong><u>Casa Batll&oacute;</u></strong></a>. Further down the avenue is one of Gaud&iacute;'s most famous buildings, Casa Mil&agrave; , also known as <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Casa-Mila--La-Pedrera/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xeLgp-ZB17gfo"><strong><u>La
Pedrera</u></strong></a>.</p>

<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="Casa Batll&oacute;" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-896-Imagen/C.Batllo.Gaudi.Barcelona.2.jpg"><br /><br />
<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="La pedrera" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-634-Imagen/Pedrera.Barcelona.2.jpg">

<p align="justify">The <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Sagrada-Familia-neighbourhood/_xMCfM9AMDl_lKCezjRpMoML_VypBgt9zSpaqShmGhIE"><strong><u>Sagrada Fam&iacute;lia</u></strong></a> (Basilica of the Holy Family) has long been a symbol of Barcelona. Gaud&iacute; began work on the monument in 1883 and several additions have been made since then.</p>

<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="Sagrada fam¨ªlia" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-869-Imagen/Sagrada-Familia.Barcelona.4.jpg">

<p align="justify">Another of his works well worth a visit is the beautiful <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Park-Guell/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xeG87SN_sB8iE"><strong><u>Park G&uuml;ell</u></strong></a>, which overlooks the city. Modernisme, however, is not synonymous with Gaud&iacute;, and one can discover many other modernist buildings and monuments throughout Barcelona, such as the exceptional <a href="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/Palau-de-la-Musica-Catalana/_3Ngb8YjSpL3U56ScBHOWcxpDev_Vr2xezc62Se8LgJI"><strong><u>Palau de la M&uacute;sica Catalana</u></strong></a>, a work of the architect Dom&egrave;nech i Montaner.</p>

<img style="width: 741px; height: 254px;" alt="Park G&uuml;ell" src="http://www.barcelonaturisme.cat/files/5445-2310-Imagen/Park-Guell.1.Barcelona.jpg"><br /><br>

